   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>To start the entire cullet system:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>At the Belt Conveyor Control screen, display the Silofeeding Cullet screen.</li>
                  <li>Turn on the entire system by pressing the <uicontrol>Start </uicontrol>button. </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note">
                  <p>If only the belt conveyor must be started, such as for maintenance, skip this
                     step and go to Step 2 below. </p>
               </note>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_wb3_4sn_vcc">
                     <image href="word/media/image9.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_ucx_jxn_vcc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To start the belt conveyor:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Make sure that the belt conveyor and safety mechanisms are in fault-free condition and functioning correctly.</li>
                  <li>Switch on the belt conveyor using the lockable main switch at the control cabinet.</li>
                  <li>Acknowledge the emergency stop using the user interface at the control cabinet.</li>
                  <li>Place in Manual mode to start the belt. </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_kds_rsn_vcc">
                     <image href="word/media/image10.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_lvb_lxn_vcc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To turn off the belt conveyor:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Shut down the belt conveyor using the user interface at the control cabinet.</li>
                  <li>The belt conveyor continues to run and terminates the movements of the actuators/</li>
                  <li>Switch off the belt conveyor using the lockable main switch.</li>
                  <li>The belt conveyor is now switched off. </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_osk_ssn_vcc">
                     <p>
                        <image href="word/media/image11.jpg"
                               placement="break"
                               id="image_bml_mxn_vcc"
                               align="center"/>
                     </p>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>LO/TO the belt conveyor using the lockable main switch at the
               disconnect.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
